What you need to know:

In the formula passed on Thursday, each county will, in this financial year, receive the exact amount it received in 2019/20 financial year.The committee came up with a revenue allocation ratio, pegged at Sh316.5 billion, and an eight-weight parameter for sharing the Sh370 billion the counties will receive in the next financial year.The formula will use data from the 2019 population census and the 2015/16 Kenya Integrated Household Budget Survey poverty index.